e-mail
b-tree
a-record

----------------------------------------------------

[
	"e-mail\r\nb-tree\r\na-record"
]

----------------------------------------------------

Kebab-case identifiers whose first component is a single hex letter (a-f) must not
produce a number token for that letter or an operator token for the hyphen.
Without the (?!-[a-z]) guard, `e` would be consumed as a number, leaving `-mail`
as a new segment where `(?<![a-z])-` would falsely match as an arithmetic operator.
